<item>
            <title>[LU-9180] Upstream ko2iblnd does not work with map_on_demand &lt;256</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9180</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I tried to set a map_on_demand = 32 (default for OPA) with an upstream Lustre build and run it on an MLX QDR set of system. &#160;When I tried a bulk&#160;lnet-selftest test, it failed with this log:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;[ 1125.547100] LNetError: 22552:0:(o2iblnd_cb.c:1068:kiblnd_init_rdma()) RDMA is too large for peer 192.168.1.24@o2ib (131072), src size: 1048576 dst size: 1048576&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When I went back to a much older upstream build, 4.8rc2, the same test worked. &#160;So, some porting from master to upstream seems to have not worked. &#160;The same test works fine on master.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
