                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="236284" author="simmonsja" created="Sat, 3 Nov 2018 18:38:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This was due to left overs from &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7650&quot; title=&quot;ko2iblnd map_on_demand can&amp;#39;t negotitate when page sizes are different between nodes.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7650&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7650&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; which was incorrect. All the code has been removed upstream and replaced with what landed during 2.11 development cycle.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="194358" author="doug" created="Wed, 3 May 2017 18:29:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This ticket is about upstream staging and not master. &#160;Upstream has it&apos;s own set of problems.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="194357" author="bogl" created="Wed, 3 May 2017 18:27:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Dmitry,&lt;br/&gt;
Failure introduced in master by &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5718&quot; title=&quot;RDMA too fragmented with router&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5718&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5718&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fix may have been fixed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9420&quot; title=&quot;Bad Check slipped into repo&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9420&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-9420&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, just landed.  Maybe you should retry on latest master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="194354" author="dmiter" created="Wed, 3 May 2017 18:07:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks this is common issue. I reopened&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5718&quot; title=&quot;RDMA too fragmented with router&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5718&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5718&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#160;because of I got this error with latest master build after patch &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5718&quot; title=&quot;RDMA too fragmented with router&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5718&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5718&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; o2iblnd: multiple sges for work request&quot; landed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="188142" author="simmonsja" created="Mon, 13 Mar 2017 19:10:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Strange it should work. The patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7650&quot; title=&quot;ko2iblnd map_on_demand can&amp;#39;t negotitate when page sizes are different between nodes.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7650&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7650&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; was never revverted upstream. Instead I expected that once a proper solution for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7650&quot; title=&quot;ko2iblnd map_on_demand can&amp;#39;t negotitate when page sizes are different between nodes.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7650&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7650&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; was done the fix could be pushed upstream instead.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
